    • Constructor Detail

      • WirelessPrinter

        public WirelessPrinter()
        Create a new printer. The printer initially has a cartridge that is half full and no paper.

      • WirelessPrinter

        public WirelessPrinter(double newInk,
                       int newPaper)
        Creates a new printer with specified amount of ink and paper
        Parameters:
        newInk - Initial ink level: must be between 0.0 and 1.0, inclusive.
        newPaper - Initial paper level: must be between 0 and 500, inclusive.

    • Method Detail

      • print

        public void print(int pagesWanted)
        This method simulates printing a given (set in the WirelessPrinter class). If there is not enough paper in the tray, the printer will stop when the paper runs out, and the remaining job is cancelled. If ink runs out during the printing processes, the printing will not stop, and the remaining pages printed will be blank.
        Parameters:
        pagesWanted - The requested number of pages to be printed.

      • loadPaper

        public void loadPaper(int pages)
        load the paper. The number of pages in the tray can not surpass its capacity.
        Parameters:
        pages - The number of pages of papers added. Pages must be equal or greater than 0.

      • replaceCartridge
